Allen Investment Management LLC Buys 123,807 Shares of Monsanto Company (NYSE:MON)

					Posted by Anthony Sawyer on Jul 23rd, 2017 // No Comments 


Tweet












Allen Investment Management LLC increased its stake in  Monsanto Company (NYSE:MON) by 26.4% during the first quarter, Holdings Channel reports. The institutional investor  owned 593,356 shares of the basic materials company’s stock after buying an additional 123,807 shares during the period. Monsanto makes up   4.0% of Allen Investment Management LLC’s investment portfolio, making the stock its 12th largest position. Allen Investment Management LLC’s holdings in Monsanto were worth $67,168,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
Other large investors also recently modified their holdings of the company. HighPoint Advisor Group LLC increased its stake in shares of  Monsanto by 11.4% in the fourth quarter. HighPoint Advisor Group LLC now owns 2,472 shares of the basic materials company’s stock valued at $286,000 after buying an additional 253 shares in the last quarter.  Whalerock Point Partners LLC increased its stake in  Monsanto by 9.0% in the fourth quarter. Whalerock Point Partners LLC now owns 6,080 shares of the basic materials company’s stock worth $640,000 after buying an additional 500 shares during the period.  Becker Capital Management Inc. increased its stake in  Monsanto by 47.9% in the fourth quarter. Becker Capital Management Inc. now owns 345,298 shares of the basic materials company’s stock worth $36,329,000 after buying an additional 111,810 shares during the period.  Teachers Advisors LLC increased its stake in  Monsanto by 4.4% in the fourth quarter. Teachers Advisors LLC now owns 1,253,117 shares of the basic materials company’s stock worth $131,840,000 after buying an additional 52,555 shares during the period.  Finally, Kentucky Retirement Systems acquired a new stake in  Monsanto during the fourth quarter worth approximately $3,344,000. 74.87% of the stock is owned by hedge funds and other institutional investors. 


 Get Monsanto Company alerts:



Shares of Monsanto Company (MON) opened at 117.38 on Friday. Monsanto Company has a 52-week low of $97.35 and a 52-week high of $118.97. The stock has a market cap of $51.57 billion, a PE ratio of 25.35 and a beta of 1.08. The company’s 50-day moving average price is $117.61 and its 200-day moving average price is $114.05. 




Monsanto (NYSE:MON) last announced its earnings results on Wednesday, June 28th. The basic materials company reported $1.93 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, topping analysts’ consensus estimates of $1.74 by $0.19. The company had revenue of $4.23 billion for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $4.18 billion. Monsanto had a return on equity of 45.26% and a net margin of 14.11%. Monsanto’s revenue for the quarter was up 1.0% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period in the previous year, the firm earned $2.17 earnings per share.  Analysts expect that  Monsanto Company will post $4.89 earnings per share for the current year. 
The business also recently announced a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Friday, July 28th. Stockholders of record on Friday, July 7th will be given a dividend of $0.54 per share. This represents a $2.16 dividend on an annualized basis and a dividend yield of 1.84%. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Wednesday, July 5th. Monsanto’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is presently 46.75%. 
